bayern.steinbrecher.gruen2.generator

Class AddressGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • bayern.steinbrecher.gruen2.generator.AddressGenerator

  • public class AddressGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a generator for generating a table of member with their names, addresses and their saluttaion. The salutation uses given nicknames instead of the real name.
    Author:
    Stefan Huber

      • generateAddressData

        public static java.lang.String generateAddressData(java.util.List<Member> member,
                                                   java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> nicknames)
        Generates a String representing a CSV-file of member with their addresses and their salutation. It also contains column labels and you can import it into Word for serial letters.
        Parameters:
        member - The member to generate output for.
        nicknames - The nicknames to use for addresses.
        Returns:
        The content for the output CSV file.
